Can't find a match. You could try to customize Nick Curtis' [Catalunya Choo Choo](http://web.archive.org/web/20140426101907/http:/www.ffonts.net/Catalunya-Choo-Choo-NF.font) and "borrow" the /r to some " [Helvetica](http://web.archive.org/web/20140426101907/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/linotype/helvetica)-Compressed-Black-like": [Inserat](http://web.archive.org/web/20140426101907/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/inserat) ( [British Inserat](http://web.archive.org/web/20140426101907/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/itfmecanorma/british-inserat) looks decent to me), [Haettenschweiler](http://web.archive.org/web/20140426101907/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/haettenschweiler), [Plakette](http://web.archive.org/web/20140426101907/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/plakette), [Compacta](http://web.archive.org/web/20140426101907/http:/www.myfonts.com/search/compacta)  
Alternatives: [Mercano Empire](http://web.archive.org/web/20140426101907/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/device/mercano-empire), [Skaiki](http://web.archive.org/web/20140426101907/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/ef/skaiki)

As sidenote, your request is a [duplicate](http://web.archive.org/web/20140426101907/http:/typophile.com/node/115950) so next time you'd like to bump simply post in the former to get it top-listed again.
Thanks a lot! I was thinking to draw my self.
